import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='pressure', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'mean={data["pressure"].mean():.2f}')
    plt.axvline(data['pressure'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f'median={data["pressure"].median():.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    sns.scatterplot(x='pressure', y='temperature', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between temperature and pressure?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
